# inline-comments-valid.json.meta — provenance sidecar (#347 W1c2, #398).
#
# Canonical `gh api repos/o/r/pulls/N/comments` REST-page payload shape used to
# drive `chp_list_inline_comments`. The `--paginate` stub emits this array once
# (equivalent to a single-page REST response); the leaf's paginate → slurp →
# normalize pipeline still runs the merge/sort pass, so the normalized-ascending
# + line // original_line fold assertions exercise identically against a
# single-page fixture. Multi-page completeness is proven by the parity suite
# (tests/unit/test-w1c2-incidental-read-parity.sh), not this focused verb
# check.
#
# The fixture is intentionally OUT-OF-ORDER by created_at to prove the leaf
# sorts, and carries a mix of {line: N}, {line: null, original_line: N}, and
# {line: null, original_line: null} rows to prove the leaf-side
# `line // original_line // null` fold at normalization time.
